Aggregation
The aggregation rule here is two-folds: - Representations are aggregated as: \[ h_c = \sum_{k \in C_{j}} \frac{\zeta_k}{\sum_{k \in C_{j}} \zeta_k}h_k\] where \(\zeta\) is the shapely value.
The Classification heads are aggregated as: \[  w_k^{(t+1)} = w_{k, R}^{(t)} - \lambda \eta_2 \sum_{\ell \in C_{j}} a_{k, \ell} (w_{k,R}^{(t)} - w_{\ell, R}^{(t)})\]

